{
  "stem": "13313.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "At the age of six-- so I'm talking now in 1938-- the-- I was enrolled in a-- in grade one in a special type of Jewish day school, which is little different from the systems we have in North America.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That kind of school would have two curriculums, or curricula, whichever way you say that.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the-- and there would be two principals-- one for the official, regular, secular curriculum and then one for the Jewish curriculum with Hebrew teachers and principal.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That school was quite a famous school called the Tachkemoni school.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It-- it was reopened after the war.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It still exists and is going strong.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, yes, yes, yes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The choice was that in those days Belgium was still a bilingual country.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There are still two languages, but it's not bilingual anymore.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The northern part is unilingually Flemish, which is a Dutch dialect, and the southern part is unilingually Walloon which is a French dialect.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But in those days, it was totally bilingual.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You could choose the language of your education no matter where you lived.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my dad said, well, we're going to alternate.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In grade one, you're going to go to the French-- Flemish curriculum.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Grade two, French, and then go back and forth like that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So that's how I kept switching from the Dutch system to the French language system.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "What was the effect on that for you?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The effect was-- was-- was-- there are many effects.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But what I remember the most was that since we had two ethnic groups that have always been at odds with each other, which would be a long story, goes back in history as far as the Roman occupation, believe it or not, the-- but both sides were very, very nationalistic.",
      "word_count": 51
    }
  ],
